<F P=101> Federal </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Warns of Consequences of Air Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Warns of Consequences of Air Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104122594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1155 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104122594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 11 April (TANJUG) -- The Yugoslav Army's 
General Staff today stated that the bombardment of civilian and 
military targets in the Srpska republic carried out by the NATO 
air force last night was an act that might bring about 
unforeseeable military consequences. 
  The Yugoslav Army is following the developments caused by 
this aggressive act. Bearing in mind the latest circumstances, 
all necessary measures have been taken to protect the 
territorial integrity of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia, the 
Yugoslav Army's General Staff says in its statement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-8123 </DOCNO>
