<F P=100> THE FORMER YUGOSLAV REPUBLIC OF MACEDONIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Denies Greek Troop Movements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Denies Greek Troop Movements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0904154494 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 9 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0904154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our Skopje correspondent Takis Dhiamandis has 
reported that the Defense Ministry of Skopje [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] has denied reports about 
an alleged concentration of Greek armed forces along its 
northwest borders. These reports have been circulating for the 
past few days. Moreover, it was one of the issues Skopjean 
President Kiro Gligorov raised in his interview with the French 
newspaper LE MONDE. 
  Tension was noticed in Skopje last night after reports began 
coming from Gevgelija, which is near the border, about the 
movement of a Greek tank column. The Defense Ministry of Skopje 
issued a statement late last night that stressed that these 
reports are not consonant with the facts. 

</TEXT>

