<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies Hosting `Arafat-Peres Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Denies Hosting `Arafat-Peres Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104114494 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1000 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1104114494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In connection with the news item broadcast last 
night by the Israeli Television and quoted by AFP, according to 
which a meeting between PLO leader Yasir `Arafat and Israeli 
Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres will be held in Bucharest on 15 
April, a possibility assessed by Palestinian sources in Tunis as 
not very likely, our correspondent Eugen Baboi, who is 
accredited to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, contacted 
Ministry spokesman Mircea Geoana, who said the following: The 
Romanian Foreign Ministry has no knowledge of such an event. 
The Foreign Ministry sent an invitation to `Arafat and Peres to 
participate in the proceedings of the Crans Montana Forum that 
will be held in Bucharest on 21-24 April, but it is still 
waiting for confirmation regarding the participation of the two 
officials. Therefore, the Romanian side cannot comment on the 
information regarding an `Arafat-Peres meeting in Bucharest on 
15 April because it has no knowledge of such a meeting. 

</TEXT>

