<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iraq Releases Four Romanians From Prison </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iraq Releases Four Romanians From Prison </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104120294 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
1000 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1104120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Four Romanian citizens who had been condemned in 
Iraq for entering that country illegally were released this 
morning from a prison near the Iraqi capital of Baghdad. The 
pardon decree was signed last night by Iraqi President Saddam 
Husayn, following a request by Romanian President Ion Iliescu. 
  A press release received from the Romanian Ministry of 
Foreign Affairs notes that the message addressed in this respect 
by the head of the Romanian state to his Iraqi counterpart was 
handed over yesterday to Iraqi Prime Minister Ahmad Husayn 
Khudayyir by Marcel Dinu, secretary of state with the Ministry 
of Foreign Affairs and special envoy of Romania's president. 
  The names of the four citizens are Danila Dumitru, Nicolae 
Aghachi, Florin Boiga, and Gabriel Encea. The formalities for 
bringing the four of them back to Romania with the assistance of 
the TAROM company are being completed by the Romanian Foreign 
Ministry through Romania's embassies in Baghdad and Amman. Their 
arrival in Bucharest is scheduled for 13 April at 1400 on a 
TAROM flight from Amman. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

