<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nastase Said To Recruit Army Chiefs for PDSR </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nastase Said To Recruit Army Chiefs for PDSR </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204103294 Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI in Romanian 6 Apr 
94 p 4 </F>

<F P=103> AU1204103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest EVENIMENTUL ZILEI </F>
<F P=105>  Romanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Radu Stefanescu report: "PDSR Is Forcing the </F>
Politicization of the Romanian Army"] 
  [Text] The leadership of the Social Democracy Party of 
Romania [PDSR], in the person of its executive chairman, Adrian 
Nastase, has begun a sustained offensive intended to politically 
enroll the Romanian Army. This action of the ruling party is 
openly backed by Minister of National Defense Gheorghe Tinca and 
tacitly supported by the head of the general chief of staff, 
Lieutenant General Dumitru Cioflina. 
  During the recent electoral tour of Adrian Nastase, also 
nicknamed "Sweety" [Bombonel], he tried to make the army 
division heads and even the army commanders join the PDSR. 
Specific similar cases were reported in Buzau and Craiova. 
  After a strong rapprochement with the East, Gheorghe Tinca 
accepts the excessive politicization of the army personally 
attending to the PDSR's electoral actions, along with the head 
of the chief of General Staff. After the elimination of [former 
Defense Minister] Lieutenant General Niculae Spiroiu, the chiefs 
of the National Defense Ministry departments were actually 
expecting a concentrated counteroffensive from the PDSR. 
Currently that counteroffensive is stronger than ever, and the 
"mastermind" behind this politicization campaign being none 
other than Adrian Nastase, also nicknamed "Sweety." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

