<H3> <TI>   Boross Cited on AWACS During Gorazde Attack </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Boross Cited on AWACS During Gorazde Attack </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104185694 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1600 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hungarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Prime Minister Peter Boross has visited 
Szekesfehervar. According to our correspondent, the prime 
minister said NATO AWACS planes have been and do remain in 
Hungarian airspace; they were here during the NATO air strike on 
Gorazde, too. However, he said, Hungary had received assurances 
that the planes are here without target guiding tasks 
[tuezvezerlesi feladatok] and that they carry out only airspace 
patrolling duties. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

