<H3> <TI>   Serbs Say UN Now Directly Involved in War </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Say UN Now Directly Involved in War </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104172894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1658 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104172894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 11 Apr (TANJUG) -- The NATO air force and 
Muslim formations in the area of Gorazde carried out 
synchronized attacks against Serb positions between 1415 and 
1445 today, the information service of the Srpska republic army 
general staff has said in a statement. 
  The statement says that the Srpska republic army 
"successfully responded to the strong attack and is holding its 
positions." 
  A NATO C-130 transport carrying a NATO rapid intervention 
unit with a large quantity of ammunition, weapons, and military 
equipment, landed at Tuzla airport at 1650, the statement says. 
  The general staff of the army of the Srpska republic has 
learned from reliable sources that rapid intervention forces 
with their weaponry and equipment have been sent from 
Frankfurt's NATO base to operate together with members of the 
Muslim force against Serb units, the statement says. 
  The synchronised attack in the Gorazde area and the abuse of 
Tuzla airport as a military means (the airport is yet to be 
opened to humanitarian operations) indicates that UN Protection 
Forces [UNPROFOR] units have overstepped their mandate and that 
they bear all responsibility for further escalation of conflict 
in the area of the former Bosnia-Herzegovina, the statement says. 
  It adds that the UNPROFOR's present activities fully confirm 
the assumption that they have openly sided with the Muslim 
forces and become directly involved in the civil war in the area 
of the former Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

