<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Future of Negotiations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Future of Negotiations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104145594 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1322 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104145594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Obrenovac, 11 Apr (TANJUG) -- Momcilo Krajisnik, the 
president of the Srpska republic assembly, said today that the 
bombing of Gorazde was a great blow to peace, which was within 
reach. 
  We are not ruling out fresh strikes, but if there are any, 
we 
will take certain political and military steps, Krajisnik said. 
  However, we cannot abandon Gorazde because before the war 35 
percent of its residents were Serbs. We cannot watch and do 
nothing while the Muslims are constantly mounting provocations 
from all three protected areas. This is what happened this time 
as well. The world should know that this area will never be calm 
unless the causes of the conflict are removed; and they lie in 
the Muslim violations of the agreement on protected areas. 
  Answering a question by a Radio Obrenovac [in Serbia] 
journalist, of whether yesterday's events will influence 
diplomatic activity and postpone the negotiations, Krajisnik 
said: We cannot remain indifferent to what the Muslims are 
trying to do, but despite everything, we have not closed the 
door on negotiations and on establishing peace. 

</TEXT>

