<H3> <TI>   Srpska Army Command Denies Shelling Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Srpska Army Command Denies Shelling Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104152694 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1505 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1104152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, April 11 (TANJUG) -- The general staff of 
the Bosnian Serb Republic Army reported Monday that its 
artillery "was not shelling Gorazde at all and that therefore 
UNPROFOR [UN Protection Forces] troops, representatives of 
humanitarian organizations or the civilian population cannot be 
in danger there". 
  "The Moslem war propaganda is hastily launching new fraud 
from Gorazde, calculated to call for and justify the engagement 
of the NATO airforce against the Serb people and army. It seems 
as if some senior UNPROFOR officers and officials have joined in 
the Moslem propaganda deceptions", the statement given to TANJUG 
says. 
  NATO U.S. warplanes on Sunday evening launched air strikes 
on 
Bosnian Serb positions near the Moslem enclave of Gorazde, a 
U.N.-designated "safe haven" which should have been 
demilitarized last spring. In late March, about 10,000 Moslems 
from Gorazde surged into a heavy offensive against Serb 
territories. 
  Moslem fabrications about attacks on Gorazde fuel hasty 
decisions on the use of force by the NATO aviation and 
contribute to the escalation of war. This prevents and 
postpones a lasting and complete cessation of hostilities and 
the reaching of an agreement on lasting peace in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

