<H3> <TI>   SRNA: NATO Bombed Muslim Part of Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SRNA: NATO Bombed Muslim Part of Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204123394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1122 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204123394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 12 Apr (TANJUG)--One of the two "F-18" 
planes attacking Serb positions around Gorazde yesterday bombed 
the town center by mistake, it has been learned from a radio 
message sent by a UN monitor to the pilot, which was intercepted 
at a radar base in neighboring Yugoslavia, SRNA reported early 
this morning. This caused panic among the people of Gorazde and 
Muslim soldiers who began to flee toward the surrounding hills. 
  Several inhabitants of Gorazde who made it to Serb positions 
said that the explosion of a bomb caused a horrific scene, large 
number of casualties and huge material damages. 

</TEXT>

