<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb Prisoners Killed by Refugees From Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Prisoners Killed by Refugees From Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104153794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1447 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 11 Apr (TANJUG) -- At least 10 prisoners 
of Serb nationality who have been detained in a silo in Tarcin, 
30 km southwest of Sarajevo, for nearly two years were killed 
last night when refugees from Gorazde broke into the prison, 
which is under the control of the Muslim authorities. 
  Serb intelligence sources say that Muslim refugees from 
Gorazde, who are living in Tarcin and the nearby village of 
Pazaric, had held the silo under blockade since Friday. The 
refugees demanded the lynching of the detained Serbs. 
  The Muslim police had the situation under control until 
Sunday evening when the mob broke into the prison and killed at 
least 10 Serbs, using firearms and other objects. 
  Muslim Sarajevo radio confirmed that the incident had 
happened, saying that shooting had been heard amid a totally 
chaotic situation, after which -- according to the radio -- 
three prisoners were missing. 
  The radio reporter says that it is assumed that there had 
been some casualties, but does not give the figure. 
  Nothing is known about the fate of the survivors of the 
massacre, but Muslim sources claim that the police again took 
control of the silo-prison. 
  The Serb side has been trying for 18 months now to organize 
the release of over 200 prisoners from the silo on the principle 
"all for all" with the Muslim authorities, and with the help of 
international humanitarian organizations, but the Muslim 
authorities have rejected all attempts to exchange prisoners. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-8193 </DOCNO>
