  [Excerpts] Cajnice, 12 Apr (TANJUG) -- According to the 
command of the Bosnian Serb Herzegovina Corps, a paramedic team 
was hit in the American bombing raid on civilian targets and 
positions of Herzegovina Corps soldiers yesterday instead of 
tanks, as NATO representatives claimed. 
  Milomir Ceranic and Radomir Maljevic, paramedics from Gacko, 
were killed on this occasion. Two houses in the Serb village of 
Bare, two km south of the Gorazde town center on the right bank 
of the Drina river, were also destroyed. [passage omitted] 
  No one was killed in the attack launched by American planes 
on Preljuca [15 km south of Gorazde] but one passenger car was 
destroyed. Serb forces' tanks were not hit in this attack 
either, contrary to claims by NATO representatives. [passage 
omitted] 

