<H3> <TI>   Hungarian Vessels Allowed To Leave Vidin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hungarian Vessels Allowed To Leave Vidin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204102594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0800 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1204102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Totka Ninova] </F>
  [Text] The two Hungarian tugs Vac and Egzsenek have just 
set sail from the Vidin bank of the Danube. The two vessels 
were detained by representatives of the Western European Union, 
the Bulgarian State Navigation Inspectorate, and Vidin customs. 
The vessels had to stay there for four days so that they could 
be provided with the necessary UN permits allowing them to sail 
to Hungary. The two vessels are towing five barges loaded with 
991 tonnes of phosphate. 

</TEXT>

