political situation in Slovakia. 
  Talbott handed personal greetings from Bill Clinton to 
President Kovac. President Clinton considers that a prosperous 
and democratic Slovakia is beneficial for the United States. 
The U.S. deputy secretary of state praised the interest of our 
state in the Partnership for Peace program and Slovakia's 
integration efforts, which enjoy the full support of the United 
States. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

