<H3> <TI>   Arbnori Notes Need for Cooperation With Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arbnori Notes Need for Cooperation With Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0904170294 Tirana ATA in English 1030 GMT 9 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0904170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 9 (ATA) -- The speaker of the 
Albanian Parliament, Pjeter Arbnori, met on April 8 with the 
head of the Turkish delegation to the Parliamentary Assembly of 
the Black Sea Economic Cooperation [BSEC], Mr. Ibrahim Atvinli. 
  "It is a fact that Albania and Turkey, as two friendly 
peoples, have the same views regarding BSEC, Mr. Arbnori said 
expressing the need of a greater cooperation between the two 
parliaments, especially in the field of legislation. 
  Mr. Ibrahim Atvinli said that the visit to a friendly 
country 
as Albania is of special delight to every Turk, especially now 
that it is following the path of democracy with devotion. In 
every international forum, Mr. Atvinli said, Turkey supports the 
foreign policy of Albania, which is an actor of peace and 
stability in the region. The strengthening of our parliamentary 
relations, he said in conclusion, will surely help the promotion 
of cooperation in economy and other sectors. 

</TEXT>

