<H3> <TI>   Finsberg, CE Delegation Arrive for Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finsberg, CE Delegation Arrive for Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Berisha Briefs Visitors on Reform </H4>

<F P=102> AU0704192594 Tirana ATA in English 1021 GMT 7 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0704192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 7 (ATA) -- "Albania is grateful to 
the Council of Europe [CE], its member states, and the European 
institutions for the assistance it has received from them," 
President Berisha said in a meeting he had yesterday at the 
presidency with the Council of Europe delegation headed by Lord 
Finsberg. 
  President Berisha said that as it has been asserted "the 
reforms in Albania have been advancing quicker than in other 
countries in the past two years," adding that Albania fulfills 
all the conditions for becoming a member of the Council of 
Europe: free elections, observation of the human rights and the 
rights of national minorities. "Albania is determined in 
further cooperation with the Council of Europe and its 
integration into Europe," President Berisha emphasized. 
  Lord Finsberg appreciated the profound changes made in the 
course of reforms and said he would like to see Albania be as 
soon as possible a full member of the Council of Europe. 

</TEXT>

