BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 8 (ATA) -- The delegation of the ad 
hoc committee of the Council of Europe led by Lord Finsberg, met 
on April 7 with the Albanian foreign minister, Alfred Serreqi. 
Mr. Finsberg took interest in the new dimensions of the 
Albanian policy, the events in Kosova and the stand of Albania 
towards Kosova and in Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia -- FYROM]. 
  "Albania's integration into Europe is a priority of the 
Albanian foreign policy," Mr. Serreqi said, adding that Albania 
is making great changes and overcoming the grave consequences of 
the communist dictatorship. 
  "We appreciate the aid and support by the european union", 
said Mr. Serreqi. "We are resolute and convinced of a 
successful cooperation with Europe". 

</TEXT>

