<H3> <TI>   Danube Embargo Monitors Stop Hungarian Vessel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Danube Embargo Monitors Stop Hungarian Vessel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804161494 Sofia BTA in English 1547 GMT 8 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0804161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vidin, April 8 (BTA) -- Representatives of the 
Western European Union, the Customs Service and the local 
division of the State Shipping Inspectorate last night arrested 
the Hungarian ship "Vac" which, together with the "Egzsenek," 
tow five phosphate-laden barges. The cargo was found to lack 
the required UN permits. The ship has been detained until the 
case will be cleared up, said Vladimir Zubarev, chief of the 
State Shipping Directorate in Vidin. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

