<H4>    Falbr Expects `Nothing Pleasant' </H4>

<F P=102> AU1104122194 Prague CTK in English 2348 GMT 8 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104122194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 9 (CTK) -- The new chairman of the 
Bohemian and Moravian Chamber of Trade Unions (CMKOS), Richard 
Falbr said today the speech which Premier Vaclav Klaus delivered 
at the CMKOS congress on Friday [8 April] indicated that 
"nothing nice and nothing pleasant is awaiting us." 
  "I would like to create a team of people who would be good 
opponents to our social partners (the government and employers) 
who sometimes do not behave like partners," Falbr told the 
delegates shortly after his election. 
  He promised to do everything to improve union activity. "I 
will proceed from the achievements of the Bohemian and Moravian 
Chamber of Trade Unions," he stressed. 
  The congress continues at 9:00 a.m. today. The names of the 
four deputy chairmen to be elected by the CMKOS Assembly during 
the night are to be announced on Saturday [9 April]. Falbr is 
expected to deliver a speech after the delegates approve 
congress documents. 

</TEXT>

