<F P=102>   AU1204100794 Prague CTK in English 1842 GMT 11 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204100794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 11 (CTK) -- Leaders of the Czech 
Social Democratic Party (CSSD) presented its deputies with a 
recommendation to initiate a constitution-based revision of the 
employment law, Vojtech Matejicny from the CSSD press department 
told CTK today. 
  Before being passed by parliament, the employment bill was 
criticized by the unions who organized an Old Town Square 
demonstration on March 22 to highlight their reservations 
against the possibility of a repeated conclusion of 
limited-period work contracts and an article allowing pregnant 
women to work night shifts. 
  Parliament passed the bill the day after. The coalition and 
the Liberal Social National Party supported the bill while the 
opposition including the CSSD voted against it. Czech President 
Vaclav Havel signed the law on April 6. 

</TEXT>

