<H3> <TI>   ODS Rejects Proposal on Administrative Units </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ODS Rejects Proposal on Administrative Units </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204082994 Prague CTK in English 1754 GMT 11 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204082994 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 11 (CTK) -- The Civic Democratic 
Party (ODS) Executive Council, at its meeting today, rejected a 
document submitted by Chairman of the Civic Democratic Alliance 
(ODA) Jan Kalvoda to ODS Chairman and Czech Premier Vaclav 
Klaus, ODS Deputy Chairman Petr Cermak told journalists. 
  The document to serve as a basis material for coalition 
talks 
on higher self-administrative units was bad and the ODS 
Executive Council was disappointed with it, Cermak said. 
  He said that the document "did not reflect things which had 
been long agreed upon" and was not acceptable to the ODS. The 
document "was conceptually empty, incomplete, not oriented 
towards the future and practically makes it possible for higher 
territorial administrative units to start functioning only 
around the year 2000," Cermak added. 
  If the political will to agree on the system of elections to 
the Senate, the as yet non-existent upper chamber of the Czech 
parliament, is shown, the ODS will not object to senatorial 
elections being held this autumn simultaneously with local 
elections, Cermak said. Judging by the state of preparation for 
the establishment of higher self-administrative units the ODS 
considered the elections to these units being held in 1996, as 
proposed by the ODA, unacceptable, he said. 

</TEXT>

