<H3> <TI>   Army Search for `Camouflaged' Political Officers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Search for `Camouflaged' Political Officers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104115494 Prague CTK in English 1420 GMT 10 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 10 (CTK) -- Defense Minister Antonin 
Baudys announced on NOVA TV today that had completed a list of 
former army "political officers" who, on the basis of a December 
1989 order by then Czechoslovak Defense Minister Miroslav Vacek, 
were "dispersed and camouflaged by a wide variety of methods" 
throughout the army. The list took six months to compile, 
Baudys said. 
  "A range of personnel measures are only now before us," he 
said, adding that 1994 would be the most significant year for 
the transformation of the armed forces. Units are finally being 
reorganized, at last creating "the right situation" for 
replacing some officers, he added. 
  Baudys also said the army was prepared to launch a 
recruiting 
campaign in search of leaders at the company and platoon level 
for drilling soldiers and strengthening discipline, especially 
in the handling of weapons. 

</TEXT>

