<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denounces Afula Massacre </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Denounces Afula Massacre </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804200494 Prague CTK in English 1622 GMT 8 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0804200494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 8 (CTK) -- The Czech Foreign Ministry 
denounces Wednesday's [6 April] massacre in the north Israeli 
town of Afula in which innocent people, including women and 
children, were killed, says a statement given to CTK today. 
  The militant Islamic organization Hamas said in its 
statement 
the Afula attack was retaliation for the massacre in Hebron in 
the occupied West Bank in February in which a Jewish extremist 
shot dead 29 Palestinians. The Afula massacre claimed the lives 
of seven people and of the attacker himself, and 50 people were 
wounded. 
  The Ministry "is opposed on principle to the solution of 
problems by the use of violence and terrorist actions which only 
aggravate the situation in the Middle East," the statement says 
and expresses support for political settlement on the basis of 
dialogue. 
  "The Israeli-Palestine agreement the implementation of which 
has been the subject of intensive negotiations indicates a 
suitable way of solving the situation," the statement says. 

</TEXT>

