<H3> <TI>   Minister on Czech-Israeli Military Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister on Czech-Israeli Military Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0804182294 Prague CTK in English 1341 GMT 8 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0804182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 8 (CTK) -- Israel and its defense 
industry are among serious applicants for close cooperation with 
the Czech Republic, Defense Minister Antonin Baudys told 
journalists today. 
  "We bear in mind that the Israeli military industry is 
state-of-the-art," said Baudys who met Israeli deputies Orri Orr 
and Moshe Nissim today. However, it would be premature to speak 
about concrete cooperation in this field, he added. 
  Baudys discussed army modernization, relations between armed 
forces and parliament, military buildup and acquiring public 
confidence with the Israeli deputies. 
  "The meeting was very useful" because Orr is a former senior 
Israeli military officer "with a very successful military record 
so that he can consider the problems both from the military and 
parliamentary views," Baudys stated. 
  Orr and Nissim, who arrived in the Czech Republic for a 
one-week visit on April 4, also met the Federation of Jewish 
Communities. 

</TEXT>

