<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Boross: Airspace Not Used for NATO Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Boross: Airspace Not Used for NATO Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204072494 Budapest MTI in English 2020 GMT 11 Apr 94 -- 
FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204072494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 11 Apr (MTI) -- During his trip to Fejer 
county today, the prime minister was at a press conference where 
he was asked whether the AWACS aircraft would have to leave 
Hungary after NATO's Sunday attack on Bosnian Serb positions. 
  The reporter reminded the prime minister of his statement 
made in February to foreign journalists -- that Hungary would 
not like NATO's aircraft to use its airspace when bombing 
military targets in Bosnia. The prime minister was also quoted 
as saying that during an air attack the AWACS aircraft should 
leave the country. 
  "Hungary's airspace has not been used for military actions 
against Bosnian targets. And this is the key issue," the prime 
minister said in his answer. 
  The February statement expressed Hungary's determination not 
to allow its airspace to be used for concrete military actions 
or controlling attacks on Serbia, he continued. 
  "We have received clear-cut guarantees that the function of 
the AWACS aircraft will be only to monitor Bosnian airspace," 
the prime minister added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

