<H3> <TI>   U.S. General Continues Visit, Talks on NATO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. General Continues Visit, Talks on NATO </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Talks With Tinca Reported </H4>

<F P=102> AU0604153794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1202 GMT 6 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0604153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 6/4/1994 -- Wednesday, 6 April, 
the talks started between Romanian Defense Minister Gheorghe 
Tinca and General George Joulwan, supreme commander of the 
allied forces in Europe, who is now on a documentation visit in 
Romania. The agenda, Romanian Army sources say, includes 
matters related to the participation of Romania and other East 
European countries in the Partnership for Peace program, the 
evolution of the democratic process in Romania and the parallel 
reform of the army, to matters concerning European and 
international security. 
  Attending the talks are Dumitru Cioflina, secretary of state 
at the National Defense Ministry and chief of the general staff, 
Ioan Mircea Pascu, secretary of state for defense policies and 
external relations of the National Defense Ministry, and other 
military officials accompanying the guest. 
  In the morning of 6 April General George Joulwan was 
received 
by the president of Romania, Ion Iliescu. 

</TEXT>

