<F P=102>   AU1204101194 Prague CTK in English 0554 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 12 (CTK) -- U.S. Undersecretary 
of State Strobe Talbott will meet with top Slovak politicians in 
his one-day visit to the capital today. He will be received in 
the morning by President Michal Kovac, then meet in the 
afternoon with Premier Jozef Moravcik, Parliament Chairman Ivan 
Gasparovic, and Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan. Talbott and 
Kukan will hold a press conference at the conclusion of their 
meeting. 
  Kukan says in the Slovak press that Talbott's visit is 
significant not only because of his close personal relationship 
with President Bill Clinton, but as a signal with regard to the 
current situation in Slovakia. He says he expects his 
discussion with Talbott to revolve around international 
questions and Slovakia's economic situation, particularly in 
regard to opportunities for American capital and businesses. 

