-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 11/4/1994 -- Commenting NATO's 
air raids against the Serbian positions in Bosnia-Herzegovina, 
the Embassy of the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia in Bucharest 
says that "deciding for armed actions, the United Nations has 
abandoned the role of peace maker which it used to play, and 
overtly sided with the Muslims," which questions the nature and 
the mandate of the UNPROFOR (United Nations Protection Force) in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, the embassy states in a press release. 
  The statement released for the press writes that the 
Yugoslav 
Embassy is definitely against the policy of pressure and 
ultimatum, against armed attacks over the Serbian area, and 
pleads that double standard policies should be renounced. 

