<H3> <TI>   Serbian Forces at Kosovo-FYROM Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbian Forces at Kosovo-FYROM Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1104104494 Tirana ATA in English 1025 GMT 11 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1104104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pristina, April 11 (ATA) -- Great forces of the 
Serbian Army, armoured vehicles and other military facilities 
have been deployed in the Han of Elez, near the 
Kosova-Macedonian border. In the Peldenica village in the same 
zone, four other armoured vehicles have been sent, the 
information centre of Kosova reports. It also says that Serbian 
police has made a check point in a road that links some villages 
with the town of Hani i Elezit. It controls Albanian citizens 
who travel in the villages of the border zone. Three tanks have 
been staying in Ura e Kashanit. Serbian military forces in 
these areas are provoking citizens and plundering them, the 
information centre says. 
  Movements and concentrations of the Serbian military and 
police forces are noticed near Gjakova, bordering Albania. 
  Serbian information sources report that the commander in 
chief of the Yugoslav Army, Momcilo Perisic, stayed several days 
in Kosova "on a visit to the units of the Pristina army corps" 
and to control the fighting readiness of the units in the 
terrain. 

</TEXT>

