<H3> <TI>   Sanctions Officials Meet WEU Representatives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sanctions Officials Meet WEU Representatives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304075894 Sofia BTA in English 1759 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1304075894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia BTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vidin, April 12 (BTA) -- The representatives of the 
Bulgarian state institutions controlling the implementation of 
sanctions along the Danube and the officials of the Western 
European Union [WEU] ended their formal meeting. 
  The participants focussed on the measures that would ensure 
efficient control over the application of sanctions along the 
Danube and specified the actions which the teams of the WEU and 
the Bulgarian institutions should take in case of embargo 
busting, BTA was told by Vasko Vasilev, deputy head of the Vidin 
Customs. 
  The representatives of Bulgaria and the WEU shared the 
opinion that each specific conflict should be resolved by 
peaceful means in order to protect the population and the 
population centres and prevent any environmental disaster along 
the river. 
  It was agreed that a similar meeting should be held in 
Bucharest, where the WEU representatives would talk with 
Romania's governmental commission to specify the actions to be 
taken in a case of embargo busting and their coordination by the 
Bulgarian, Romanian and WEU teams. 

</TEXT>

