<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havel on NATO Strikes as `Last Real Warning' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Havel on NATO Strikes as `Last Real Warning' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204204094 Prague CTK in English 2010 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 12 (CTK) -- Czech President Vaclav 
Havel firmly believes that the April 10 NATO bombing raid 
against the Bosnian Serb positions around Gorazde will be the 
last real warning that would bring the Bosnian Serbs to the 
negotiating table, Havel told CTK and the daily RUDE PRAVO today. 
  "I have long thought is was necessary that the international 
community use stronger means to let it be known that (the Serbs) 
cannot do whatever pleases them," Havel said. 
  Two U.S. Air Force F-16 jets under NATO command attacked 
Bosnian Serb units which had entered the southern suburbs of 
Gorazde. It was the first NATO air strike against ground 
targets in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

