<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   SDL Spokesman on NATO's `Dangerous Game' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDL Spokesman on NATO's `Dangerous Game' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204191494 Prague CTK in English 1650 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April (CTK) -- The NATO air strikes on 
Bosnian Serb positions on Sunday and Monday are a dangerous 
game, foreign policy spokesman of the Democratic Left Party 
(SDL) Zdenek Masopust said at a party press conference today. 
  NATO was looking for a new identity and was not yet able to 
take into account that in the post-communist world Russia plays 
an important role, he said. He emphasized that Russia should 
not be humiliated for fear of "feeding nationalist extremism" in 
the country. 
  NATO fighters attacked Bosnian Serb positions on Monday 
afternoon in an attempt to prevent a Serb advance on the Bosnian 
town of Gorazde, a UN designated "safe haven". The strike came 
less than 24 hours after a Sunday strike against Bosnian Serbian 
positions. Russia strongly protested against both attacks, as it 
did against the NATO ultimatum to the Serbs besieging Sarajevo. 
  At the same conference SDL deputy Vladimir Rezac pointed out 
possible conflicts between the post-1989 Land Law and its 
amendments and the decrees of post-war Czechoslovak President 
Eduard Benes. He said it is often overlooked that the Benes 
decrees were ratified by the Czechoslovak parliament in 1946, 
making them constitutional. Hence the return of land formerly 
belonging to "German Nazis" living in Czechoslovakia who were 
deprived of their land by the Benes decrees might be illegal, he 
said. 
  Rezac referred in particular to the case of Karl Des Fours 
Walderode, who was granted Czech citizenship again last year. 
Walderode was a member of Konrad Henlein's Sudeten German Party, 
adopted German citizenship in 1939 and joined the Wehrmacht. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

