<H3> <TI>   Vondra Returns From Syria, Pakistan, Iran </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vondra Returns From Syria, Pakistan, Iran </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204130894 Prague CTK in English 1139 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 12 (CTK) -- First Deputy Foreign 
Minister Alexandr Vondra pointed today to the crucial importance 
of Syria, Pakistan and Iran which exceeds the scope of the 
region from the power, political and economic points of view. 
Vondra, who returned from a twelve-day trip to the three 
countries, also pointed to their large markets which make them 
attractive for European partners. 
  Czech politicians and entrepreneurs should pay more 
attention 
to these countries because privatization has been advancing 
there and local economies are adapting themselves to the new 
budgetary and taxation policy, Vondra said. 
  Despite changes in the political climate in the past on both 
sides, the long-term traditions of good commercial relations 
with these countries have remained. It would be erroneous not 
to take this into account and not to strive to maintain and 
develop all the good moments in the tradition of mutual 
relations, he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

