<H3> <TI>   Nastase Presents PDSR Social-Economic Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nastase Presents PDSR Social-Economic Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204181894 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1554 GMT 12 Apr 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1204181894 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest ROMPRES, 12/4/1994 -- The ruling Party of 
Social Democracy (PDSR), presented a document at a Tuesday, 
April 12, press conference of the party treating about the 
social-economic priorities of the PDSR programme, that were 
proposed for discussions with economic experts of other parties. 
  The eight chapters of the document, said PDSR Executive 
Chairman Adrian Nastase, refer to the main objectives of the 
economical-social activity, to the speeding up of privatisation, 
to in-depth restructuring of the fiscal and budgetary policy, to 
the monetary and hard-currency policy, to the putting in place 
of the objectives and priorities regarding foreign economic 
relations, to measures aimed to further the reform in the other 
sectors of the social activity, in fields such as the salary 
policy and welfare. 
  The PDSR executive chairman said that the governing party 
was 
aware of its responsibilities and it would show responsibility, 
consistence, interest as far as the country's destiny is 
concerned, in order to translate into deeds the guiding lines 
and priorities of the economical-social strategy, with a view to 
continue the consolidation of the state of law and ensure real 
social security. 

</TEXT>

