<H3> <TI>   Berov `in Quarantine'; Hepatitis Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berov `in Quarantine'; Hepatitis Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304084094 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0800 
GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1304084094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Bulgarian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After repeated queries on our part, a few minutes 
ago Raycho Raykov, head of the government Press Center, issued 
the following announcement: 
  Having recuperated from his cardiac bypass operation on 12 
March, Professor Berov began taking an active part in the work 
of the Council of Ministers on 7, 8, and 10 April. 
  According to information received at 0900 on 13 April from 
Dr. Todor Gerasimov, head of Lozenets Hospital, the condition of 
the prime minister's cardiovascular system and blood circulation 
continues to be stable. 
  However, on 11 April a change in Prof. Berov's health 
condition was noted. The clinical conclusion was that there was 
the possibility of hepatitis. Specialized laboratory tests are 
under way and the results will be published in a day or two. 
  According to Dr. Gerasimov, because of the development of a 
clinical picture of the hepatitis virus, Prof. Berov is in 
quarantine. He will have no personal contacts in the next few 
days. 

</TEXT>

