<H3> <TI>   Serb Delegation Postpones Scheduled Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serb Delegation Postpones Scheduled Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1104211494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
2000 GMT 11 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1104211494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The negotiations between a Croatian delegation and 
representatives of the Serb authorities from the UN-protected 
areas, scheduled to resume tomorrow, will not materialize. 
  Nobody wants to make any guesses about the reasons behind 
the 
postponement of the negotiations or about a possible new date 
when they could take place. Slavko Degoricija, member of the 
Croatian delegation, said that the Croatian delegation is ready 
for the next round of talks and stressed that the resumption of 
the talks depends on the decision of the Serb representatives. 
Economic and social issues were to be discussed in this round 
of the negotiations. 

</TEXT>

