<F P=106> [TA SR report: "They Need Quality Statistics"] </F>
  [Text] Bratislava--Michal Kovac, president of the Slovak 
Republic, appointed Stefan Condik chairman of the Slovak 
Statistical Office. The newly appointed chairman of the Slovak 
Statistical Office took over the letter of appointment 
yesterday, in the presence of Prime Minister Jozef Moravcik. 
The president of the Slovak Republic stressed that the 
Statistical Office chairman has the professional qualifications 
to execute this important post. He drew attention to the fact 
that, in the process of transformation, the government and other 
central bodies require statistical data of high quality. 

