<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   New National Property Fund Presidium Elected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New National Property Fund Presidium Elected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204130694 Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY in Slovak 7 Apr 
94 p 2 </F>

<F P=103> AU1204130694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava HOSPODARSKE NOVINY </F>
<F P=105>  Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [TA SR report: "National Property Fund Presidium in New </F>
Composition"] 
  [Excerpts] Bratislava--An extraordinary 28th meeting of 
the National Council of the Slovak Republic [NRSR] was convened 
yesterday, on the initiative of NRSR Chairman Ivan Gasparovic, 
to decide on the composition of new supreme bodies of the 
National Property Fund [FNM] of the Slovak Republic. [passage 
omitted] 
  The deputies decided by secret ballot that Rudolf Janac will 
be president of the FNM Presidium and Viliam Vaskovic vice 
president. A total of 92 ballots were distributed; the two votes 
were then held separately. Rudolf Janac, who had been proposed 
by the Party of the Democratic Left [SDL], received 77 votes, 
and Viliam Vaskovic (proposed by the "Center" coalition) won the 
support of 76 deputies. 
  A third secret ballot determined that Zoltan Zimmermann 
(Christian Democratic Movement), Pavol Kinces (Center), Juraj 
Kamaras (Center), Karol Pittner (SDL), Frantisek Szomolay 
(Coexistence/Hungarian Christian Democratic Movement), and Igor 
Mathe (Movement for a Democratic Slovakia) became members of the 
FNM Presidium. No other candidate won the needed more than 50 
percent of vote. The seventh member of the FNM Presidium will 
therefore be elected at the next meeting of parliament. 
  After the promulgation of the results of the secret ballot, 
NRSR Chairman Ivan Gasparovic declared the extraordinary meeting 
of parliament closed. The next, 29th, NRSR extraordinary 
meeting, which will open on 12 April, will be devoted to the 
Slovak Government's Policy Statement. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

