<H3> <TI>   Rugova Condemns Greek `Act of Terror' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rugova Condemns Greek `Act of Terror' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204193294 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1800 
GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1204193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Albanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The massacre by Greek terrorists on Albanian 
soldiers has caused outrage among the Albanian people of Kosova, 
a telegram from President Rugova sent to Albanian President Dr. 
Sali Berisha reads. 
  We strongly condemn this act of terror and ask the 
international community to draw Greece's attention to it and 
condemn the insurgency of terrorist groups in the Republic of 
Albania, the telegram states. 
  We urge Greece and the Greek people -- who, along with the 
Albanians, is the most ancient people in the Balkans -- to be 
more reasonable and contribute to good neighborliness with the 
Albanians. 
  Both personally and in the name of the people of the 
Republic 
of Kosova, President Rugova expressed his condolences and 
support to the families of the deceased. 

</TEXT>

