<H3> <TI>   Serbs Agree to Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Agree to Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304154594 Paris AFP in English 1529 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1304154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, April 13 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serbs have 
agreed to a ceasefire around the Moslem enclave of Gorazde, 
Russian special envoy Vitaliy Churkin said Wednesday [13 April]. 
  According to the Bosnian Serb SRNA news agency, Churkin said 
after a meeting with Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic at his 
Pale headquarters that the "accord should help lead to a general 
ceasefire between Moslems and Serbs." 

