<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cajnice, 12 Apr (TANJUG) -- NATO aircraft overflew 
Serb positions around Gorazde several times late this afternoon 
and this evening, dropping to only 1,000 meters, but did not 
engage in combat actions, the command of the Herzegovina Corps 
has announced. 
  The Muslims again tried to take advantage of the low-flying 
U.S. aircraft, launching a fierce attack from the direction of 
Gorazde on the positions of the Herzegovina corps in the region 
of Jardiste and Majdan. Their infantry attack was supported by 
artillery fire. 
  As the command of the Herzegovina corps announced, the 
attack 
has been repelled while the Muslim units, having suffered huge 
losses, were returned to their starting positions. One Serb 
fighter was killed and two others wounded in the attack. 

</TEXT>

