<H3> <TI>   Izetbegovic Responds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Izetbegovic Responds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1204191094 Paris AFP in English 1842 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1204191094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, April 12 (AFP) -- Late Tuesday [12 
April] Izetbegovic questioned Rose's assertion that Moslem 
soldiers inside Gorazde had shelled Bosnian Serb positions. 
  "We have sufficient reasons to doubt the reliability of 
General Rose's sources," the Bosnian president said in a 
statement. 
  He also criticised the fact that Rose had not specified 
whether the Moslem mortar fire had been in response to a Serb 
attack or a defensive manoeuvre. 
  Izetbegovic said UNPROFOR had "systematically... denied" 
Bosnian reports on the serious nature of the Serb offensive 
against Gorazde, adding that the NATO air strikes had been 
launched too late and that their "limited and selective nature 
has only encouraged the enemy." 
  Serb shells had killed 23 people in Gorazde Monday, he said. 
  Izetbegovic said he was willing to return to the negotiating 
table provided Serbs withdrew from all areas of the eastern 
Bosnian enclave they had conquered and a political solution was 
found which did not legitimise "the occupation of Bosnia." 

</TEXT>

