<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serbs Seek Condemnation of NATO `Aggression' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Serbs Seek Condemnation of NATO `Aggression' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1204135394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1233 GMT 12 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1204135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>
<F P=105>  Serbo-Croatian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 12 Apr (TANJUG) -- The government of the 
Srpska republic today expressed indignation at the United 
Nation's effective involvement in the civil war in 
ex-Bosnia-Herzegovina and its siding with the Muslim side, the 
ministry for information of the Srpska republic has stated. 
  The government draws attention to the already looming risk 
of 
this act leading to the very brink of a conflict of cataclysmic 
proportions and maintains that there is no need to emphasize the 
fact that the United Nations has undermined the relatively 
reasonable logic of the hitherto peace process by taking this 
action. 
  Apart from the necessary measures, derived from its powers 
and taken in keeping with the latest situation, the government 
has also decided to acquaint in detail the international public 
with the consequences of the bombardment of the Serb positions 
around Gorazde. 
  In this context, the ministry for foreign affairs of the 
Srpska republic will inform Russia, Germany, China, Japan, and 
India in particular about the NATO aggression and demand of 
these countries to condemn this aggression and support the peace 
process. 
  Taking into account all the elements of the civil war, a 
formula for peace in ex-Bosnia-Herzegovina must recognize the 
right to self- determination of all three peoples, including 
their right to have their own state, the lifting of sanctions 
against Yugoslavia and the Serbian people in general, a lasting 
cessation of hostilities, the disengagement of the warring 
parties under the supervision of the United Nations and 
territorial demarcation, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

