<H3> <TI>   Greek-Language Paper Calls For `Friendship' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Greek-Language Paper Calls For `Friendship' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304072594 Tirana ATA in English 1018 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1304072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, April 12 (ATA) -- President Berisha has 
received a letter from the publisher and the editorial board of 
the newspaper LLAIKO VIMA, a paper published in Gjirokaster in 
the Greek language for the Greek minority. The letter follows: 
  The April 10 incident in the border point of Peshkepi e 
Siperme grieved all the employees and readers of this paper. 
Acts of this kind, wherever they come from, have nothing to do 
with the sincere feelings of the peoples and the desire of the 
Greek minority in Albania to play the role of the bridge and 
factor of friendship between the Albanian people and the Greek 
one. 
  We believe in the will to clarify this incident to the end 
in 
order not vanish hopes for relations of good neighbourliness. 
  On this occasion we also express our profound and most 
sincere condolences to the families of the victims, who were 
unjustly killed. Our paper offers the families of the victims a 
modest sum of 80,000 new leks in support. 

</TEXT>

