<F P=101> Albania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crossing Border With FYROM Made Easier </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crossing Border With FYROM Made Easier </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304074094 Tirana ATA in English 1036 GMT 12 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1304074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lindita Karadaku] </F>
  [Text] Tirana, April 12 (ATA) -- Since April 11, the 
border crossing point of Tushemisht in the border between 
Albania and Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia 
-- FYROM] has begun a 24-hour service for the crossing of 
nationals from both sides and of small vehicles, such as cars 
and other means of transportation. 
  Whereas the Qafe-Thane border point, known for the long line 
of vehicles and people waiting to cross the border, will 
continue to work for 24 hours like before, but only for trucks. 
  This change intends to facilitate the crossing of the border 
by nationals and vehicles, according to a source close to the 
Albanian Ministry of Public Order. 
  According to a note published today by the newspaper 
RILINDJA, the Macedonian Ministry of Interior has confirmed this 
change in a communique, as well. 

</TEXT>

