<F P=102>   AU1304174394 Prague CTK in English 1645 GMT 13 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1304174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 13 (CTK) -- The Czech Government view 
of the NATO air strikes against Bosnian Serb targets near 
Gorazde on April 10-11 was identical to the Foreign Ministry's, 
Premier Vaclav Klaus told journalists after a cabinet meeting 
today. 
  In a communique issued on Monday [11 April] the Foreign 
Ministry supported the United Nations and NATO decision to bomb 
Bosnian Serb positions near Gorazde in Bosnia. 
  At the meeting the government approved Klaus's visit to 
South 
America. Klaus will visit Chile, Brazil and Argentina. Klaus 
said the government considered Latin American countries to be 
very important markets for the Czech Republic and the territory 
where problems similar to transformation of Central and East 
European countries were being solved. 
  Klaus will leave Prague on April 17 to return on April 27. 

</TEXT>

