<H3> <TI>   Coalition Disagrees on Local Government Powers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Coalition Disagrees on Local Government Powers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1404081194 Prague CTK in English 1804 GMT 13 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1404081194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prague, April 13 (CTK) -- The parties of the 
coalition government disagree on the powers the bodies of the 
higher local administrative units should have, Premier Vaclav 
Klaus told journalists today. 
  The government therefore decided to limit the bill on the 
competence of the higher administrative units to their powers. 
He said while there were not significant differences of opinion 
between the coalition partners on the matter of the competence 
of the higher administrative units, there were "fundamental 
discrepancies" between them concerning the competence of the 
bodies of these units. 
  The government was concerned that the powers of higher 
administrative units might expand in the future, he said. "It 
would be naive to assume that competence can be determined once 
and for all time, since higher units are living organisms," he 
said. 
  Klaus said the government would debate the narrowed down 
bill 
on the constitutional law on April 27 and submit the definitive 
form of the bill to parliament on April 30. 

</TEXT>

