<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Call For Moravcik's Resignation in Parliament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Call For Moravcik's Resignation in Parliament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1304170094 Prague CTK in English 1437 GMT 13 Apr 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1304170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, April 13 (CTK) -- "Jozef Moravcik has 
no moral right to be the Slovak premier and I therefore call on 
him to resign from his office," Tibor Cabaj, chairman of the 
Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) Deputies' Group, said 
today at parliamentary debate on the programme of the new Slovak 
Government. 
  Cabaj said that Moravcik had harmed and dishonored the 
Slovak 
Republic, pointing to a report worked out by the Slovak Foreign 
Ministry when headed by Moravcik before Slovak President Michal 
Kovac's visit to the Vatican last year. 
  The Vatican's state system was characterized in the report 
as 
a "theocratic and absolutist monarchy headed by the pope," Cabaj 
said. He said that the document also pointed to the Vatican's 
cooperation with the fascist states in the 30's. Cabaj 
described as scandalous the passage in the report saying that 
"under the pontification of John Paul II the Vatican has been 
evidently seeking to propagate the concept of Christian Europe 
and the Christian Pan-Slavism." According to the report the 
Vatican is aiming at "strengthening positions of power and the 
ideological influence of the Roman Catholic Church and is 
propagating the concept of Christian Europe, ideological and 
subversive activity and the clerical coalition with the United 
States and other NATO states," Cabaj said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

